snippet.textDisplay: I haven't commented on a coke studio song before but this is just so good I had to express my thoughts on it. Sajjad Ali doesn't cease to amaze with his magical voice even after all these years. The poise with which he navigates such unbelievably difficult notes is a real thing of beauty. And the lyrics; The melancholic expressions are strung together so beautifully. You get every bit of the pain the poet has tried to pen down. And Zaw Ali. Wow Zaw Ali. The first time she started "Jin ko majbooriye" she had me in tears. Don't know why but it was what it was. She has voice and skill way way beyond her years. I think it is safe to say Mr. Sajjad Ali has successfully transferred his magic to the next generation superstar.Good luck to both Father and Daughter.Hope to hear both of you many more times in the future. A fan for life.
